            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EDrawing%20close%20to%20the%20Lord%20should%20be%20your%20lifetime%20pursuit.%20Sometimes%2C%20however%2C%20that%20process%20is%20hindered.%20James%20writes%20about%20two%20stages%20you%20may%20have%20to%20pass%20through%20as%20you%20attempt%20to%20enter%20God's%20presence.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFirst%2C%20James%20says%20to%20%22humble%20yourselves%20before%20God%22%20(James%204%3A7).%20Pride%2C%20lust%2C%20and%20friendship%20with%20the%20world%20will%20block%20your%20prayer%20requests.%20Also%2C%20you%20may%20be%20asking%20with%20wrong%20motives%3A%20%22You%20want%20only%20what%20will%20give%20you%20pleasure%22%20(v.%203).%20However%2C%20if%20you%20humble%20yourself%20and%20submit%20your%20life%20to%20God%2C%20then%20your%20requests%20will%20be%20made%20from%20right%20motivations.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENext%2C%20James%20says%20to%20%22resist%20the%20Devil%2C%20and%20he%20will%20flee%20from%20you%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(v.%207).%20Satan%20may%20be%20hindering%20your%20requests%20from%20coming%20to%20pass%2C%20even%20though%20God%20has%20granted%20them.%20When%20Daniel%20prayed%2C%20his%20prayer%20was%20actually%20answered%20from%20the%20first%20day%2C%20but%20Satan%20hindered%20it%20from%20coming%20to%20pass%20for%20twenty-one%20days%20(Daniel%2010%3A12-13).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAfter%20you%20humble%20yourself%20and%20resist%20the%20devil%2C%20you%20will%20be%20able%20to%20%22draw%20close%20to%20God%2C%20and%20God%20will%20draw%20close%20to%20you%22%20(James%204%3A8).%20God%20loves%20you%20and%20is%20waiting%20for%20you%20to%20draw%20near%20through%20the%20gate%20of%20the%20Lord!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
